{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-25T08:06:56.888778612Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-5d9f9080","body":"Task-source validation is still bypassed in direct `project.toml` readers outside `FsProjectStore`. The branch now rejects empty `milestone_id`/`bead_id` pairs in `FsProjectStore::read_project_record()` and project creation, but `workspace_governance::active_project_milestone_id()` and `validate_project_exists()` still deserialize `ProjectRecord` directly without calling `validate_task_source()` (`src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs:153-167`, `src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs:195-221`), and `sync_project_prompt_hash()` does the same in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/drift.rs:307-318`. I reproduced this with the built binary: after appending `[task_source] milestone_id = \"ms-alpha\"; bead_id = \"\"` to a project, `ralph-burning project select test-proj` succeeded and `ralph-burning milestone next` proceeded against `ms-alpha` instead of failing on corrupt metadata. Route these reads through `FsProjectStore::read_project_record()` or call `validate_task_source()` immediately after `toml::from_str()` so the new invariant is enforced consistently.","dedup_key":"371dab631b92c4f4e37fe7d0e7651174f485db8abe7c130bd5d0bf34e7433c41","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260425072224","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
